{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπιχαίρω</b>, <br /> <b>rejoice over, exult over,</b> mostly of malignant joy, with <i>dative</i> <i>of things</i>, κακοῖς τοῖς τοῦδε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 961; ἀτυχίαις τῶν πέλας 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 673, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1379b17: with _dative_ _person_, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.134; τινὶ τεθνηκότι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Eumenes” 2; ἐπί τινι 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “de Morte - Papiri Ercolanesi” 20: _absolutely_, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 1015 (_anapaest meter_), 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 9.61 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also in <i>aorist</i> I <i>middle</i>, ἐπεχήρατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 4.55 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “de Morte - Papiri Ercolanesi” 20. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> rarely in good sense, ἐπιχαρῆναι (<i>aorist 2</i> <i>passive</i>) <b>rejoice in</b> another's <b>joy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 314 (Lyric poetry): with _accusative_, σὲ μὲν εὖ πράσσοντ᾽ ἐπιχαίρω 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 136 (_anapaest meter_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>take pleasure in,</b> with <i>dative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 6.14. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7471","accentedUnicode":"ἐπιχαίρω","shortDef":"to rejoice at","mediumDef":"to rejoice at","stepGloss":"to rejoice at","stepTransliteration":"epichairō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}